        "eyebrow": "OUR STORY",
        "heading": "Long Island Born. Colorado Made. No Shortcuts.",
        "body": "<p>Since 2014, we've brought authentic New York Italian food to Colorado and made believers of millions of people. We moved out here in 2006 straight from Long Island's Nassau County, quickly learning that the food we knew and loved simply didn't exist here — after suffering through 50+ pizzerias from Pueblo to Wyoming.</p><p>Faced with an ultimatum from his wife Tracey — \"find authentic food or move back\" — Antonio committed to mastering the craft of pizza. He built a drive-thru coffee shop just outside Rocky Mountain National Park where customers would pull up, smell fresh pizza instead of coffee, and declare it the best food in town. Then the historic 1,000-year floods of 2013 reshaped everything — and that's when Antonio went all-in.</p><p>It's never \"just pizza\" at Antonio's. The dogged pursuit of excellence led to Antonio being inducted into the World Pizza Champions team in 2021, becoming a published author in 2024, and taking 2nd place at the International Pizza Expo for World's Best Cheese Slice. Out of 50. In the world.</p>",
        "stat1": "Since 2014",
        "stat2": "#1 in Colorado",
        "stat3": "World Pizza Champions",
        "stat4": "2 Colorado Locations",
        "cta_text": "Order Now",
        "cta_url": ""
      }
